{{Infobox museum | name = Gemma Museum | native_name = | native_name_lang = | image = Germa museum.jpg | imagesize = 200 | caption = Cave art exhibited at the Germa Museum | map_type = | map_caption = | map_alt = | coordinates = | established = | location = [[Fezzan]], [[Libya]] | type = [[archaeological museum]] | collection = [[Garamantes|Garamantian]] items | visitors = | director = | president = | curator = | publictransit = | car_park = | network = | website = }} The '''Germa Museum''' is an [[archaeological museum]] located in [[Fezzan]], [[Libya]]. It contains old objects excavated at [[Germa]], the seat of the ancient [[Garamantian Kingdom]].<ref>{{cite web|author=Temehu.com |url=http://www.temehu.com/Cities_sites/museum-of-germa.htm |title=Germa Museum |publisher=Temehu.com |date= |accessdate=2012-10-07}}</ref> The Garamantian Kingdom flourished between 400 BC and 600 AD.
