'''Hartwig Altenmüller'''<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.uni-hamburg.de/Wiss/FB/09/ArchaeoI/Aegypto/altenmul.htm |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2013-05-03 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070212145119/http://www.uni-hamburg.de/Wiss/FB/09/ArchaeoI/Aegypto/altenmul.htm |archivedate=2007-02-12 |df= }} Hamburg University biography (in German)</ref> (born 1938, in [[Saulgau]], [[Württemberg]], [[Germany]]) is a [[Germany|German]] [[Egyptologist]]. He became professor at the Archaeological Institute of the [[University of Hamburg]] in 1971. He worked as an archaeologist in [[Saqqara]] from 1969 to 1982, and then the [[Valley of the Kings]] (where he worked on [[KV13]], [[KV14]] and [[KV47]]) from 1984 to 1998, retiring in 2003.

==Publications==
