[[File:Summer Solstice Sunrise over Stonehenge 2005.jpg|300px|right|thumb|Megalithic sunrise]]
'''Megalithomania''' is an annual conference on [[megalithic]] culture held at the Glastonbury Assembly Rooms, [[Glastonbury]] in [[England]].<ref>[http://www.forteantimes.com/features/commentary/3796/megalithomania_2010.html Fortean Times Article - Megalithomania 2010 - Unrecognised pyramids, Eden and Egypt, landscape zodiacs and archaeoacoustics] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101231001915/http://www.forteantimes.com/features/commentary/3796/megalithomania_2010.html |date=31 December 2010 }}</ref> It was named after the book by [[John Michell (writer)|John Michell]] of the same name<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=RCwSAQAAIAAJ&q=John+Michell,+Megalithomania!+%281982%29&dq=John+Michell,+Megalithomania!+%281982%29&hl=en&ei=Xgl7TcHfMs2BhQff6_jnBg&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=1&ved=0CDAQ6AEwAA Michell, John F., Megalithomania: artists, antiquarians, and archaeologists at the old stone monuments, Cornell University Press, 157 pages, 1982]</ref> and organized by Hugh Newman, Gareth Mills and John Martineau.  Notable speakers have included [[John Michell]], [[Graham Hancock]], [[David Hatcher Childress]], [[Gordon Hillman]], Michael Tellinger, [[John Major Jenkins]], [[Robert Bauval]], [[Robert K. G. Temple]], [[Paul Devereux]], and [[Andrew Gough]]. [[Megalithic]] art is displayed and visits to such locations as [[Stanton Drew]], [[Stonehenge]] and [[Avebury]] have been organized.<ref>[http://www.forteantimes.com/strangedays/events/1068/megalithomania_conference.html Fortean Times Article - Megalithomania Conference - What were the ancients up to?] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110711020755/http://www.forteantimes.com/strangedays/events/1068/megalithomania_conference.html |date=11 July 2011 }}</ref><ref>[http://www.forteantimes.com/features/fbi/380/megalithomania.html Harpur, Merrily., Fortean Times Article - Megalithomania, August 2006] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101231071003/http://www.forteantimes.com/features/fbi/380/megalithomania.html |date=31 December 2010 }}</ref> Lectures are often captured on [[video]] and distributed around the [[internet]]. The latest Megalithomania in South Africa has employed [[live streaming]].

==2013==
The list of speakers at the 2013 Megalithomania conference at the Glastonbury Assembly Rooms in [[Glastonbury]] included [[Robert Schoch]], [[Andrew Collins (author)|Andrew Collins]], [[Michael Glickman]], [[Gary Bitcliffe]], [[Maria Wheatley]] and [[Hugh Newman]]. It took place on 18 and 19 May and includes a range of field programs to visit ancient sites.

