{{Other uses|Saeculum (disambiguation)}}
{{Infobox journal | title = Saeculum | editor = | discipline = | peer-reviewed = | language = German, English, French | abbreviation = Saeculum | publisher = Böhlau Verlag | country = Germany | frequency = Biannual | history = 1950-present | openaccess = | license = | impact = | impact-year = | website = http://www.boehlau-verlag.com/0080-5319.html | link1 = | link1-name = | link2 = | link2-name = | cover = | former_names = | JSTOR = | OCLC = | LCCN = | CODEN = | ISSN = 0080-5319 | eISSN = | boxwidth = }}
'''Saeculum''' (latin time, century) is a German [[scholarly journal]]. It was launched in 1950 by the historian [[Georg Stadtmüller]] and was originally published by Verlag Karl Alber.<ref>{{cite journal|title=Title Page|journal=SAECULUM: Jahrbuch für Universalgeschichte|date=1950|volume=1|issue=1|pages=I-II}}</ref> Since 2003 it has been published by Böhlau Verlag.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=http://www.boehlau-verlag.com/0080-5319.html|title=Böhlau Verlag|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref>
Subtitled "Jahrbuch für Universalgeschichte", the journal is devoted to [[world history]] and mainly focuses on [[Social history|social]], [[Economic history|economic]], and [[cultural history|cultural]] aspects.<ref>Website of the editorial office at [https://www.uni-goettingen.de/de/saeculum/558929.html Georg-August-Universität Göttingen] - Saeculum, 2017-05-02</ref> It features a wide variety of topics by scholars from various disciplines. An editorial published in 2013 states that it is "open to ... contributions ranging from pre- and protohistory to the present" and "to all historical topics including natural environments" and that it seeks to overcome a eurocentric perspective by publishing articles on all world regions and by encouraging comparison and the observation of transcultural entanglements.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Paul|first=Axel T.|date=2013|title=Universalgeschichte - ein Editoral|url=|journal=Saeculum|volume=63|pages=1, 3}}</ref> According to a mission statement included in the journal's blurb, it also offers a "forum for fundamental debates" in history and [[cultural studies]].<ref name=":0" />
Saeculum is a [[peer-review]]ed journal and is published biannually. Its general editors are the German historians Peter Burschel and Christoph Marx. It publishes articles in German, English, and French.
